## Refactor permission management: app-level from Databricks, domain-level via Teams matrix

Context: Previously, the app maintained its own `.permissions.json` file that
duplicated Databricks App principals and added an internal role column.
Domain-level permissions were managed from a dropdown on the Settings page
next to a flat per-principal list. This was confusing, redundant, and did not
scale to real teams.

The new model:
1. App-level access is driven directly by Databricks App permissions
   (`list_app_principals`). No local `.permissions.json`. A user can access
   the application iff they are an App admin (`CAN_MANAGE`) OR they (or one of
   their groups) appear in the App principals. Admins bypass all further
   checks.
2. Domain-level access is strictly explicit: only members of a domain's team
   (entry in `.domain_permissions.json`) can access that domain. No entry
   means no access — no implicit minimum role.
3. The new Registry → Teams page is a matrix UI (principals × domains) with
   per-cell role selectors (—, Viewer, Editor, Builder), dirty-state tracking,
   and a single batch Save button.

Changes:

Backend (permissions + service):
1. src/back/objects/registry/permissions.py
   - Removed all `.permissions.json` I/O: `_PERMISSIONS_FILENAME`,
     `load_permissions`, `save_permissions`, `list_entries`,
     `add_or_update_entry`, `remove_entry`, `_permissions_path`, and the
     associated cache.
   - Added `ROLE_APP_USER` and exported it via `registry/__init__.py`.
   - `get_user_role()` now returns `ROLE_ADMIN` / `ROLE_APP_USER` / `ROLE_NONE`
     based on `is_admin` and Databricks App principals (users + resolved
     group memberships via SCIM).
   - `get_domain_role()` simplified: admin bypasses all checks, otherwise the
     role is exactly what is in `.domain_permissions.json` for that principal,
     or `ROLE_NONE` if absent. No more `min_role` floor.
   - Added `save_domain_permissions_batch(changes, ...)` that groups changes
     by domain and applies them transactionally per domain, returning
     `{success, saved, failed}`.
2. src/back/objects/registry/service.py — Removed `permissions_file_path()`.
3. src/back/objects/registry/__init__.py — Export `ROLE_APP_USER`.
4. src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py
   - Dropped `list_permissions_result`, `add_permission_result`,
     `delete_permission_result`.
   - `list_app_principals_result()` returns `{users, groups}` from App
     permissions, used by both the read-only Permissions page and the Teams
     matrix rows. `list_principals_result` now aliases it.
   - `build_teams_matrix_result()` returns `{domains, principals, assignments}`
     for the matrix UI.
   - `save_teams_batch_result(changes, ...)` validates input and delegates to
     `permission_service.save_domain_permissions_batch`.

Backend (routes + middleware):
5. src/api/routers/internal/settings.py
   - Removed `POST /settings/permissions` and
     `DELETE /settings/permissions/{principal}`.
   - `GET /settings/permissions` now returns `{users, groups}` (read-only).
   - Added `GET /settings/teams` (matrix payload) and `POST /settings/teams`
     (batch save).
6. src/shared/fastapi/main.py — `PermissionMiddleware` updated:
   - `ROLE_NONE` at the app level now redirects to `/access-denied?reason=app`.
   - New `_DOMAIN_SCOPED_PREFIXES` (`/domain/`, `/ontology/`, `/mapping/`,
     `/dtwin/`) are gated on `user_domain_role != ROLE_NONE` for non-admins;
     denial redirects to `/access-denied?reason=domain`.
   - Viewer write-method block now applies only inside domain-scoped routes.
   - `/settings/teams` added to admin-only prefixes.

Frontend:
7. src/front/templates/settings.html — Removed Domain-Level Permissions block
   and the Role column; the Permission List is now a read-only "App
   Principals" table with an informational banner pointing to Registry → Teams
   for per-domain roles.
8. src/front/static/config/js/permissions.js — Rewritten as a single
   read-only `loadPermissionsList()` that renders `{users, groups}`.
9. src/front/config/menu_config.json — Added `teams` item under
   Registry → Domains.
10. src/front/templates/registry.html — Loads the new Teams partial, CSS, and
    JS.
11. src/front/templates/partials/registry/_registry_teams.html (NEW) — Header,
    refresh/save buttons with dirty badge, non-admin warning, principal and
    domain search inputs, and the matrix container.
12. src/front/static/registry/css/registry-teams.css (NEW) — Sticky headers
    and principal column, dirty-cell styling, compact color-coded role
    selectors, filter hide/show classes, empty-state.
13. src/front/static/registry/js/registry-teams.js (NEW) — Matrix rendering,
    dirty-state map, unsaved-changes guards on refresh + `beforeunload`,
    batch save, principal/domain filters, `sidebarSectionChanged`
    integration.
14. src/front/routes/home.py — `/access-denied` accepts a `reason` query
    parameter and passes `user_role` / `user_domain_role` to the template.
15. src/front/templates/access_denied.html — Different messaging for
    `reason=app` vs `reason=domain`.

Tests:
16. tests/test_permissions.py — Removed legacy `.permissions.json` tests.
    Updated `TestGetUserRole` for the new admin/app-user/none model and
    `TestGetDomainRole` for the strict "entry or none" behavior. Added
    `TestSaveDomainPermissionsBatch` covering add/update/remove across
    domains, partial failures, and invalid inputs.
17. tests/test_permission_middleware.py — Added `ROLE_APP_USER` cases for
    admin-only routes and a new `TestDomainScopedRoutes` class covering:
    app-user denied on domain routes without a team role, viewer GET allowed
