### Fix: "Update from UC" refreshed every loaded table instead of the checked ones

Symptom: in the Domain › Metadata view, checking one row in the data-
sources list and clicking **Update from UC** still refreshed every
loaded table.

Root cause: `updateMetadataFromUC()` in
`src/front/static/domain/js/domain-metadata.js` built the request body
from `metadataCache.tables.map(t => t.name)` unconditionally, so the
checkbox state (`tableSelections`, which was wired only to "Remove
Selected Tables") was ignored. The `/domain/metadata/update-async`
backend already honors `table_names` when it is a non-empty list, so
the fix is entirely frontend.

Change:
- `updateMetadataFromUC()` now reads `tableSelections` and sends only
  the checked rows when any are checked; when nothing is checked, it
  falls back to the previous "update all" behavior.
- The info notification now distinguishes "Updating N selected
  table(s)…" from "Updating all N table(s)…".
- Helper text in `_domain_metadata.html` and the
  column-header / button tooltips were updated so users understand
  the checkbox column now drives both "Update from UC" and "Remove
  Selected Tables".

Modified files:
- src/front/static/domain/js/domain-metadata.js
- src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_metadata.html
